</div>

<div class="mdlz-container">
  {roundedIV === null ? (
    <div class="verdict-card" style="border-color: #ef4444;">
      <h2 style="color: #ef4444; border:none;">Data Fetch Failed</h2>
      <p>Unable to calculate intrinsic value. Missing requisite financial data.</p>
    </div>
  ) : (
    <>
      <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
      <div class="verdict-card">
        <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
        <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
        <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
        <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
          {verdictText}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${latestRev !== null ? (latestRev / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${latestFCF !== null ? (latestFCF / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${latestEps !== null ? latestEps.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-value">${netCash !== null ? (netCash / 1000).toFixed(1) + 'B' : 'N/A'}</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Net Cash / (Debt)</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
      <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
      <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to calculate intrinsic value mathematically, relying entirely on derived financial realities.</p>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
          <p>Mondelez generated <strong>${latestFCF.toLocaleString()} million</strong> in free cash flow most recently. This is the real cash produced after all capital expenditures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
          <p>We project FCF to grow at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for the next 5 years, derived mathematically from Mondelez's historical FCF CAGR.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
          <p>After Year 5, we assume a perpetual growth rate of <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>, capturing all value generated into infinity utilizing the Gordon Growth Model.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
          <p>We discount these future cash flows back to today using a discount rate (WACC) of <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>. This is derived considering the 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%) plus an equity risk premium suitable for a staple food business.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="step-num">5</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
          <p>Summing PVs gives Enterprise Value. Adding Net Cash (${netCash.toLocaleString()}M) gives Equity Value. Finally, we divide by the diluted shares outstanding ({latestShares.toLocaleString()}M) to arrive at the intrinsic value per share.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
      <h2>The Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
      <p>All core assumptions are dynamically derived from Mondelez's scraped financial reality.</p>

      <div class="assumption-grid">
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
          <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            Derived directly from the company's historical Free Cash Flow Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR), capped within reasonable limits (2-6%) for a mature consumer packaged goods operation facing current commodity environments.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
          <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            Built atop the baseline 10Y Treasury yield of 4.18%. As a defensive consumer staple (Oreos, Cadbury), MDLZ commands a lower required risk premium than cyclical tech, leading to a calculated ~8.5% required return.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
          <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
          <div class="rationale">
            Set at 2.5%, slightly trailing long-term nominal GDP growth expectations but aligning tightly with long-run inflation. It reflects pricing power against volume maturity.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
      <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
              <th>FCF ($M)</th>
              <th>PV Factor</th>
              <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Base (Latest)</td>
              <td>${latestFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
              <td>—</td>
              <td>—</td>
            </tr>
            {projectedFCF.map(p => (
              <tr>
                <td>Year {p.year}</td>
                <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
                <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
                <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
            <tr class="row-total">
              <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
              <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
      <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
              <th>Value ($M)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × {(1 + growthRateTerminal).toFixed(3)})</td>
              <td>${Math.round(projectedFCF[4].fcf * (1 + growthRateTerminal)).toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ ({(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% − {(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%))</td>
              <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="row-total">
              <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
              <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
      <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
              <th>Value ($M)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
              <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
              <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
              <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
              <td>${netCash.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>= Equity Value</td>
              <td>${equityValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
              <td>{latestShares.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="row-total">
              <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
              <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ HISTORICAL CHARTS ═══ -->
      <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>
      <p>Data successfully extracted dynamically. Here is Mondelez's recent historical performance.</p>

      {revenueHistory.length > 0 && (
        <>
          <h3>Revenue ($M)</h3>
          <div class="bar-chart">
